                <h1>Understanding the Star of David: Symbolism and Significance</h1>
                <p>The Star of David, a symbol of Judaism, features two interlocking triangles forming a hexagram. It represents the connection between God, the Jewish people, and their faith. Often seen in synagogues and Jewish art, it serves as a reminder of the enduring heritage and identity of Jewish culture throughout history.</p>
